#. type: text
#: docs/zh/triton_api/Reduction_Ops/sum.md:24
msgid "#### 2.2.2 Shape 支持"
msgstr "#### 2.2.2 Shape Support"

#. type: text
#: docs/zh/triton_api/Reduction_Ops/sum.md:26
msgid "结论：在 Shape 方面，GPU 与 Ascend 平台无差异。"
msgstr "Conclusion: There is no difference between GPU and Ascend platform in terms of Shape."

#. type: text
#: docs/zh/triton_api/Reduction_Ops/sum.md:28
msgid "### 2.3 特殊限制说明"
msgstr "### 2.3 Special Restrictions Explanation"

#. type: text
#: docs/zh/triton_api/Reduction_Ops/sum.md:30
msgid ""
"> 相对社区能力缺失且无法实现\n"
"> keep_dims=True需要测试更多规格，来确定是否全面支持。目前已测3D dim=2情况下，支持 keep_dims=True。\n"
"> `dtype` 参数当前版本暂未支持。社区 Triton 3.5.0 中，`dtype` 参数用于控制求和运算的累加数据类型：未指定时，位宽小于 32 的整数类型会自动提升为 `int32`/`uint32` 以避免溢出；显式指定时，输入会先转换为指定类型再执行求和。当前 Triton-Ascend 基于社区 Triton 3.2.0，该类型提升逻辑尚未支持，将在后续升级至 3.5.0 版本时完整支持。\n"
msgstr ""
"Relative community capability is missing and cannot be achieved.  \n"
"`keep_dims=True` requires testing on more specifications to determine full support. Currently, it has been tested and supports `keep_dims=True` in the 3D dim=2 case.  \n"
"The `dtype` parameter is not yet supported in the current version. In community Triton 3.5.0, the `dtype` parameter is used to control the accumulation data type for sum operations: when not specified, integer types with a bit width less than 32 are automatically promoted to `int32`/`uint32` to avoid overflow; when explicitly specified, the input is first converted to the specified type before performing the sum. The current Triton-Ascend is based on community Triton 3.2.0, and this type promotion logic is not yet supported. It will be fully supported in a future upgrade to version 3.5.0.\n"

#. type: text
#: docs/zh/triton_api/Reduction_Ops/sum.md:32
msgid "### 2.4 使用方法"
msgstr "### 2.4 Usage"

#. type: text
#: docs/zh/triton_api/Reduction_Ops/sum.md:34
msgid "以下示例实现了对2Dshape的tensor进行sum运算："
msgstr "The following example implements the sum operation on a 2D shape tensor:"

#. type: code
#: docs/zh/triton_api/Reduction_Ops/sum.md:36
msgid ""
"```python\n"
"@triton.jit\n"
"def tt_sum_2d(in_ptr, out_ptr,\n"
"              xnumel: tl.constexpr, ynumel: tl.constexpr, znumel: tl.constexpr,\n"
"              XB: tl.constexpr, YB: tl.constexpr, ZB: tl.constexpr, dim: tl.constexpr):\n"
"    xoffs = tl.program_id(0) * XB\n"
"    yoffs = tl.program_id(1) * YB\n"
"    xidx = tl.arange(0, XB) + xoffs\n"
"    yidx = tl.arange(0, YB) + yoffs\n"
"    idx = xidx[:, None] * ynumel + yidx[None, :]\n"
"\n"
"    x = tl.load(in_ptr + idx)\n"
"    ret = tl.sum(x, dim)\n"
"\n"
"    if dim == 0:\n"
"        oidx = yidx\n"
"    else:\n"
"        oidx = xidx\n"
"    tl.store(out_ptr + oidx, ret)\n"
"\n"
"```\n"
msgstr ""

